# Hardware Driver Rules

## CAN2USB Protocol
The RobStride CAN2USB debugger (CH340, VID:PID 1A86:7523) speaks an AT-framed binary protocol. NOT SLCAN, NOT robotell. Frame format:

```
TX/RX: 'A' 'T' [4B wire_id] [1B len] [data...] '\r' '\n'
wire_id = (29-bit arb_id << 3) | 0x04, big-endian
```

The `RobStrideBus` class in `robstride_bus.py` implements `can.BusABC` so it works with the `robstride` pip package's `Client` class.

## RS03 Motor Specs
- 60 N·m peak / 20 N·m rated torque
- 50 rad/s max speed
- 9:1 planetary gearbox, 880g
- 48V nominal (currently running at 24V on bench)
- CAN 2.0B extended frames (29-bit ID), 1 Mbps

## Motor API Pattern
`Motor` class in `motor.py` wraps `robstride.Client`. It owns-or-borrows a `RobStrideBus`. Multiple motors on the same CAN bus should share one bus instance (pass `bus=` parameter).

## Important Gotchas
- Windows console can't print Unicode emoji — use ASCII in print statements
- PowerShell escaping breaks inline Python — use script files instead
- `robstride.Client` motor_model param affects feedback scaling (model 1 vs other)
- Always disable motors in cleanup/finally blocks to prevent runaway
